[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 2 718 699, with reports of cases by 214 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.0% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 32.4% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 190 654 deaths have been reported, 186 022 (97.6%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by France, Germany, UK, Turkey, Iran, China, and Russia as number 10. - Mod.MPP]

