[More information is needed on the exact sampling methodology used as well as the sensitivity and specificity of the antibody test that was developed by the state laboratory. The results are the highest seropositivity rates of the studies performed to date, and it is staggering to think that as many as 20% of the population in New York City may have been infected already. The ethnic distribution is also curious, supporting racial disparities in infection rates previously discussed. Missing in the data now is the demographic profile of all subjects tested. I look forward to seeing the full data presentation when it is available - Mod.MPP

